<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4581381>
    dc:description "Figure 2. Male of Diahogna martensii (Karsch) from Cape Naturaliste, Tasmania, Australia (QVMAG 13:42218). (A, B) Carapace profile, dorsal and lateral views, respectively; (C) eye pattern in frontal view; (D) left male pedipalp, apical part of bulbus; (E, F) left male pedipalp, ventral and lateral views, respectively. Scale bar: 3.93 mm (A); 4.17 mm (B); 1.16 mm (C); 1.04 mm (D); 0.77 mm (E, F)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4581381/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4581379>
    dc:description "Figure 1. Photographs (dorsal view) of species of Diahogna. (A) Female of D. martensii (Karsch) from Blackmans Lagoon, Tasmania, Australia (QVMAG 13:42205); (B) female of D. exculta (L. Koch) from O’Brians Gap, Wollongong, New South Wales, Australia (AM KS58056); (C) female of D. hildegardae n. sp. from Tambo River at Doctors Flat, Victoria, Australia (WAM T48116); (D) male holotype of D. pisauroides n. sp. from Adelaide River, Northern Territory, Australia (NTMAG A485). Scale bar: 1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4581379/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4581387>
    dc:description "Figure 5. Diahogna exculta (L. Koch), male from Noumea, New Caledonia (MHNP 3877) and from O’Brians Gap, Wollongong, New South Wales, Australia (AM KS58056). (A, B) Left pedipalp, ventral and lateral views, respectively; (C) left male pedipalp, apical part of bulbus; (D, E) female epigyne, ventral and dorsal views, respectively. Scale bar: 0.81 mm (A, B); 0.63 mm (C); 0.67 mm (D, E)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4581387/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4581391>
    dc:description "Figure 7. Diahogna pisauroides n. sp., male holotype from Adelaide River, Northern Territory, Australia (NTMAG A485). (A, B) Left pedipalp, ventral and lateral views, respectively; (C) left male pedipalp, apical part of bulbus. Scale bar: 0.68 mm (A, B); 0.37 mm (C)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4581391/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

